    <h2>Why BandRadar?</h2>
    <p><b>Music.</b> Do you love live music? BandRadar tracks shows by the bands you want to see live, and then alerts you via email that a perfomance is coming up. No more scouring of different websites and newspapers for information on upcoming shows only to find you've missed the boat.</p>
<p><b>Places.</b> Maybe you live a few blocks from a cool live music venue and want to know what's what with upcoming performances. BandRadar lets you track venues as well as bands.
</p><p><b>Events.</b> Are you in a band? Manage a live music venue? BandRadar lets you edit and add information about upcoming events and new bands in town.</p>
<p>BandRadar is a Buunabet, LLC project.  Visit <a href="http://buunabet.com/">the Buunabet Group</a> for information on site development and help with building a site like BandRadar for your event tracking needs.</p>

<p>BandRadar is built using 100% OpenSource development tools.  The site sits on a server running <a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/"> Ubuntu</a>, the database is run with <a href="http://www.postgresql.org/">PostgreSQL</a> and BandRadar is built in <a href="http://www.python.org/">python</a> using a rapid development framework called <a href="http://turbogears.org/"> TurboGears</a>.  Finally, the icons you see next to the menu items are from the <a href="http://www.famfamfam.com/lab/icons/silk">FAMFAMFAM Silk Icons set</a>.</p>
 

